results.title: Live, Laugh, Lobotomy Blackwork Pattern; Snarky, Dark-Humor Cross Stitch Digital Download
results.description:
Live, Laugh, Lobotomy Blackwork Pattern

We've all seen the "Live, Laugh, Love" signs, but that might feel a little too sunshiny for some of us. This dark humor pattern acknowledges that sometimes the darker side of life can't just be smiled away. 

Lobotomies themselves have a horrific history and while some forms of the procedure still exist today (though not performed with an icepick!), it was once used to silence a wide swath of people who were labeled "different" by society. I don't want to make light of that barbarous history with this pattern, but to provide an outlet for the complicated feelings surrounding it. Mental health is a human right. 

A non-blackwork, colorblock version of this pattern is also available in my shop.

* This is a PDF pattern for you to stitch*

Finished pattern is 115 stitches wide by 128 stitches high.

Total size depends on the Aida cloth size:
    	 18ct— 6.4 x 7.1 inches (or 16.2 x 18.1 cm)
    	 16ct— 7.2 x 8 inches (or 18.3 x 120.3 cm)
     	 14ct— 8.2 x 9.1 inches (or 20.9 x 23.2 cm)

PDF includes:
		• Preview sheet with sizing info
		• Single-page symbols on color block sheet
		• Enlarged symbols on color block sheets
		• Enlarged black & white symbols sheets
		• Thread color key (DMC colors)

results.title: The Traveling Adventures of One Grocery Basket
results.description:
Here is a list of some funny "picture this/imagine that" thoughts about a traveling grocery basket.  I hope one of these images brings a smile for you today.

If you don't have the $$ to pay for this Word document, here it is below.

I wish you a good day...whether you're at work, home or...traveling...perhaps you'll capture a sighting of....one grocery basket...  :)


The Traveling Adventures of One Grocery Basket
(Something Funny is Going on Here…)
(Imagine This/Picture That!)

This is similar to the pictures I saw recently on the news about a boy who forgot his teddy bear at the airport.  The airlines crew kindly took pictures of the bear and its traveling adventures around the USA.  I thought it was very cute and quite humorous.

So, I thought I’d use my imagination and write about a grocery basket… its adventures and sightings seen at the most unusual and unexpected places.

1.	 A grocery basket at a basketball game…having a ball!

2.	 Mr. & Mrs. Basket…basking in the sun at the beach.

3.	 Playing at the city park…doing “cart”wheels.

4.	 Just being himself…. filled with items at the grocery store.

5.	 A decorative flower basket…(basket filled with colorful flowers).

6.	 Hit right in the bread basket…(a cart damaged in its center after being struck by someone trying to park).

7.	 Someone sitting on a basket (leaning on its side)…waiting at the bus stop.

8.	 Feeling the cool breeze while rolling downhill…. basket wearing a long and colorful scarf waving in the wind.

9.	 Raw and Odor – 2 baskets sitting in a court room as the jury rules a guilty verdict for transporting several illegal carryons.

10.	 The basket’s name is:  Basket Robbins.

11.	  A depressed basket (flattened after a hit and run in a parking lot).

12.	  A run-a-way basket (rolling down hill).

13.	 Earning a star at the Hollywood Walk of Fame: (picture of 4 tire tracks).

14.	 At a Catholic church during Sunday services: Baskets were constantly passing in and out of every pew.

15.	 A new television show called:  “Who Wants To Be a Million Baskets?”

16.	 A new daytime soap opera called:  All My Baskets (a drama filmed inside a 24 hour super grocery store).

17.	 A basket orgy:  Several baskets lined up in the section for “pick up”.

18.	 The 3 Baskets:  Mama basket, papa basket and baby basket.

19.	 A basket carrying on about who picked him up and took him for a ride.

20.	  After being arrested, the basket was easily picked from a lineup.

21.	 A homeless person repeating the phrase, “There’s no place like home”.

22.	 A different meaning to a bar and grill (a basket transformed into a bar-b-que cooking area at a scout’s campfire.

23.	 Basket Wings (shaped like wings of an airplane…not in a fast food restaurant).

24.	 The good, the bad and the basket.

25.	 My pet basket (a basket wearing a leash).

26.	 Taking a selfie with all of his co-workers at the store.

27.	 Taking a nude selfie (without any groceries on).

28.	 At an overnight Tupperware party…”carrying” on as usual…

29.	 Standing in a lineup at the police station as a suspect who ran over a bag lady…while rolling into some joint…(resulting in a hit and roll charge).

30.	 She had all of her eggs in one basket.

31.	 One grocery basket asking another basket loaded with 10 bags of chicken, “What’s the matter Colonel Sanders, Chicken?”

32.	 A basket slowly riding on a tight wire (balancing act) on the hit show “You’ve Got Balance!”


©Theodddoll Antics
   Esther Monsalve

results.title: Beaded Pendant Necklace: Hand-stamped; Live, Love, Laugh; Jasper, Quartz, Sea Glass, Crystal; Copper; Umber, Turquoise
results.description:
I crafted this statement necklace with three separate hand-stamped copper pieces with the words "live", "love", and "laugh".   Natural stone, including jasper and quartz; crystal; and glass, including sea glass, beads in umber, light turquoise, and ivory colors are mounted on hand-crafted copper wire links.  These are joined by copper tubing on hand-crafted copper wire links and medium sized antique copper rectangular link chain.

The necklace measures approximately 26.5 inches in length.  The dangling pendant  measures approximately 3.75 inches in length.  An antique copper colored lobster claw clasp secures the necklace.
